    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>How to Give Away $21.8 Billion</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Louise M Young letter on Jean Strouse's April 16 article holds Gates Foundation is gender balanced (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>It was mentioned that the historian Mark Dowie had some recommendations on the composition of the executive board of the Gates Foundation. One was for gender balance. With four people running the foundation and two of them women (Melinda Gates and Patty Stonesifer), I think 50-50 is a pretty good balance. Too bad more executive boards don't follow suit.</p>
        <p>Louise M. Young  New York</p>
      </block>
